To more intuitively evaluate the capability of detecting weak optical signals, the specific detectivity (D*) is defined as the reciprocal of NEP normalized by the square root of the device active area (A):3D∗=A/NEP=RA·BW/iin,N,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
